to the editor because of new york state 's arcane ballot qualification system candidates like senator john mccain who have less money and less support from the republican party machine may not be able to gather the necessary signatures to be on every primary ballot in the state editorial jan 3 you point out that different states have different rules for getting on the ballot if citizens in new york do not have the same choice of candidates in a presidential primary as the citizens in california how can the outcome be considered the will of the people for the election to be fair the laws governing ballot access for a national candidate should be national suzy sandor new york jan 6 2000

